ur ego; think for yourself, not by yourself; only connect; and don’t give up. Each chapter is chockful of real-world examples showing these principles at work—from the discovery of penicillin to the fight for trans rights—and how they lead to more thoughtful conclusions. More than a book of tips and tricks (or ways to be insufferably clever at parties), How to Think like a Philosopher is an invitation to develop the habits of good reasoning that our world desperately needs.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPhilosophy, Modern. 0aReason. 0aThought and thinking. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226826653423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226826653/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles